page_1_text=Geolosys is a mod which is meant to add difficulty to mining. Most of this manual will assume that the configs are default, but may make mention of possible config options when relevant.
page_2_text=Geolosys works on mechanics very similar to those of TerraFirmaCraft, in the sense that mineral deposits are rare and large. Unlike TFC, it aims to be compatible with as many mods as possible. Samples below §3Y=24§0 have a chance of spawning a §4Magma block§0, so be careful!
page_3_text=Samples generate on the surface, within the same chunk as the corresponding mineral vein. If the config allows, you can get a small sample of what the entire vein will yield by either right-clicking or breaking the sample. Prospecting early game might be hard, but know that once you find a sample it's within that chunk (generally in the center)! Make yourself a Prospector's Pick ASAP to make the process easier.
page_4_text=Clusters act as the ore material themselves; the ore block you find in the world is useless, but the cluster is what can be processed! If silk touching, you'll always get the cluster unless mining a vanilla-replacement which will instead yield the actual vanilla ore-block. You can use these clusters in any type of machine, and if the config allows they can also be smelted.
page_5_text=Vanilla stone variants are now clustered into large plutons, instead of generating sporadically throughout the world.
page_6_text=Added by Geolosys to work the same as Vanilla. Coal can generate between §3Y=48§0 and §3Y=70§0.
